  "monologue": "Reasoning: Given her strong need for structure and sensitivity to post-meal urges, a compact post-meal urge-action plan using non-food coping (pause, breathing, water, short movement) aligns with what has helped before while introducing a fresh, repeatable ritual. Adding a quick log reinforces memory and accountability without overwhelming her.",
  "utterance": "Great job so far. After your next meal, try a simple urge-action: pause for a moment, take a few slow breaths, drink a glass of water, and choose a light movement break (a short walk or gentle stretch). Then jot down what helped and how the craving shifted.",
  "endkey": false
}
